ùóŸKarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/book/installation.mdŸ@33b08c7531174478afa8cbf9ffaa7e537f82f33ce3246d1c0f67efd0c3745b93•next:ë≠Installing Nu⁄‘

There are lots of ways to get Nu up and running. You can download pre-built binaries from our 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/releases] release page
, 
[link: https://repology.org/project/nushell/versions] use your favourite package manager
, or build from source.
The main Nushell binary is named 
``nu``
 (or 
``nu.exe``
 on Windows). After installation, you can launch it by typing 
``nu``
.
@
[link: @snippets/installation/run_nu.sh] code
