íêê⁄Title: next:
Path: Pre-built Binaries
Content:
Nu binaries are published for Linux, macOS, and Windows 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/releases] with each GitHub release
. Just download, extract the binaries, then copy them to a location on your PATH.
óŸKarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/book/installation.mdŸ@aa569f7f92cb35236df44b9070cc5a13d29c61e4342b2c8256d95714c9cb7078•next:ë∞Package Managers⁄[Nu is available via several package managers:
[link: https://repology.org/project/nushell/versions] Packaging status
For macOS and Linux, 
[link: https://brew.sh/] Homebrew
 is a popular choice (
``brew install nushell``
).
For Windows:
[link: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/package-manager/winget/] Winget
Machine scope installation: 
``winget install nushell --scope machine``
Machine scope upgrade: 
``winget update nushell``
User scope installation: 
``winget install nushell``
 or 
``winget install nushell --scope user``
User scope upgrade: Due to 
[link: https://github.com/microsoft/winget-cli/issues/3011] winget-cli issue #3011
, running 
``winget update nushell``
 will unexpectedly install the latest version to 
``C:\Program Files\nu``
. To work around this, run 
``winget install nushell``
 again to install the latest version in the user scope.
[link: https://scoop.sh/] Scoop
 (
``scoop install nu``
)
For Debian & Ubuntu:
```Fenced(Borrowed("sh"))
wget -qO- https://apt.fury.io/nushell/gpg.key | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/fury-nushell.gpg
echo "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/fury-nushell.gpg] https://apt.fury.io/nushell/ /" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/fury-nushell.list
sudo apt update
sudo apt install nushell

```
For RedHat/Fedora & Rocky Linux:
```Fenced(Borrowed("sh"))
echo "[gemfury-nushell]
name=Gemfury Nushell Repo
baseurl=https://yum.fury.io/nushell/
enabled=1
gpgcheck=0
gpgkey=https://yum.fury.io/nushell/gpg.key" | sudo tee /etc/yum.repos.d/fury-nushell.repo
sudo dnf install -y nushell

```
For Alpine Linux:
```Fenced(Borrowed("sh"))
echo "https://alpine.fury.io/nushell/" | tee -a /etc/apk/repositories
apk update
apk add --allow-untrusted nushell

```
Cross Platform installation:
[link: https://www.npmjs.com/] npm
 (
``npm install -g nushell``
 Note that nu plugins are not included if you install in this way)
íêê⁄àTitle: next:
Path: Package Managers
Content:
Nu is available via several package managers:
[link: https://repology.org/project/nushell/versions] Packaging status
For macOS and Linux, 
[link: https://brew.sh/] Homebrew
 is a popular choice (
``brew install nushell``
).
For Windows:
[link: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/package-manager/winget/] Winget
Machine scope installation: 
``winget install nushell --scope machine``
Machine scope upgrade: 
``winget update nushell``
User scope installation: 
``winget install nushell``
 or 
``winget install nushell --scope user``
User scope upgrade: Due to 
[link: https://github.com/microsoft/winget-cli/issues/3011] winget-cli issue #3011
, running 
``winget update nushell``
 will unexpectedly install the latest version to 
``C:\Program Files\nu``
. To work around this, run 
``winget install nushell``
 again to install the latest version in the user scope.
[link: https://scoop.sh/] Scoop
 (
``scoop install nu``
)
For Debian & Ubuntu:
```Fenced(Borrowed("sh"))
wget -qO- https://apt.fury.io/nushell/gpg.key | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/fury-nushell.gpg
echo "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/fury-nushell.gpg] https://apt.fury.io/nushell/ /" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/fury-nushell.list
sudo apt update
sudo apt install nushell

```
For RedHat/Fedora & Rocky Linux:
```Fenced(Borrowed("sh"))
echo "[gemfury-nushell]
name=Gemfury Nushell Repo
baseurl=https://yum.fury.io/nushell/
enabled=1
gpgcheck=0
gpgkey=https://yum.fury.io/nushell/gpg.key" | sudo tee /etc/yum.repos.d/fury-nushell.repo
sudo dnf install -y nushell

```
For Alpine Linux:
```Fenced(Borrowed("sh"))
echo "https://alpine.fury.io/nushell/" | tee -a /etc/apk/repositories
apk update
apk add --allow-untrusted nushell

```
Cross Platform installation:
[link: https://www.npmjs.com/] npm
 (
``npm install -g nushell``
 Note that nu plugins are not included if you install in this way)
óŸKarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/book/installation.mdŸ@d4ce60d6d33d496b9203323362f36880bf26c740fdfd00d74e0ca1795e6ac5d7•next:ë∑Docker Container Images⁄Docker images are available from the GitHub Container Registry. An image for the latest release is built regularly

for Alpine and Debian. You can run the image in interactive mode using:
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
docker run -it --rm ghcr.io/nushell/nushell:<version>-<distro>

```
Where 
``<version>``
 is the version of Nushell you want to run and 
``<distro>``
 is 
``alpine``
 or the latest supported Debian release, such as 
``bookworm``
.
To run a specific command, use:
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
docker run --rm ghcr.io/nushell/nushell:latest-alpine -c "ls /usr/bin | where size > 10KiB"

```
To run a script from the current directory using Bash, use:
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
docker run --rm \
    -v $(pwd):/work \
    ghcr.io/nushell/nushell:latest-alpine \
    "/work/script.nu"

```
íêê⁄QTitle: next:
Path: Docker Container Images
Content:
Docker images are available from the GitHub Container Registry. An image for the latest release is built regularly

for Alpine and Debian. You can run the image in interactive mode using:
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
docker run -it --rm ghcr.io/nushell/nushell:<version>-<distro>

```
Where 
``<version>``
 is the version of Nushell you want to run and 
``<distro>``
 is 
``alpine``
 or the latest supported Debian release, such as 
``bookworm``
.
To run a specific command, use:
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
docker run --rm ghcr.io/nushell/nushell:latest-alpine -c "ls /usr/bin | where size > 10KiB"

```
To run a script from the current directory using Bash, use:
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
docker run --rm \
    -v $(pwd):/work \
    ghcr.io/nushell/nushell:latest-alpine \
    "/work/script.nu"

```
