óŸKarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/book/installation.mdŸ@fc7e749f948f3d2b18b1b93f1ba4fb6667fa9c04c8fb343bc6d618d8039a65a9•next:ë£Nix⁄∞If using 
[link: https://nixos.org/download/#nix-install-macos] Nix
 for package management on macOS, the 
``openssl``
, 
``cmake``
, 
``pkg-config``
, and 
``curl``
 packages are required. These can be installed:
Globally, using 
``nix-env --install``
 (and others).
Locally, using 
[link: https://github.com/nix-community/home-manager] Home Manager
 in your 
``home.nix``
 config.
Temporarily, using 
``nix-shell``
 (and others).
íêê⁄–Title: next:
Path: Nix
Content:
If using 
[link: https://nixos.org/download/#nix-install-macos] Nix
 for package management on macOS, the 
``openssl``
, 
``cmake``
, 
``pkg-config``
, and 
``curl``
 packages are required. These can be installed:
Globally, using 
``nix-env --install``
 (and others).
Locally, using 
[link: https://github.com/nix-community/home-manager] Home Manager
 in your 
``home.nix``
 config.
Temporarily, using 
``nix-shell``
 (and others).
óŸKarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/book/installation.mdŸ@d724ade49ec5151aa401d2609327b7bd8fe9b6e24474aa7f29ccbe2e61221baa•next:ë¨ using Cargo⁄b[link: https://crates.io] Nushell releases are published as source to the popular Rust package registry 
[link: https://crates.io/] crates.io
. This makes it easy to build and install the latest Nu release with 
``cargo``
:
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
cargo install nu --locked

```
The 
``cargo``
 tool will do the work of downloading Nu and its source dependencies, building it, and installing it into the cargo bin path.
Note that the default plugins must be installed separately when using 
``cargo``
. See the 
[link: ./plugins.html#core-plugins] Plugins Installation
 section of the Book for instructions.
íêê⁄ãTitle: next:
Path:  using Cargo
Content:
[link: https://crates.io] Nushell releases are published as source to the popular Rust package registry 
[link: https://crates.io/] crates.io
. This makes it easy to build and install the latest Nu release with 
``cargo``
:
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
cargo install nu --locked

```
The 
``cargo``
 tool will do the work of downloading Nu and its source dependencies, building it, and installing it into the cargo bin path.
Note that the default plugins must be installed separately when using 
``cargo``
. See the 
[link: ./plugins.html#core-plugins] Plugins Installation
 section of the Book for instructions.
óŸKarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/book/installation.mdŸ@1b56e0f589ae69e569bf1c5d11cf86a882a5ec9679827306ef430cfee4ceae6d•next:ëŸ#Building from the GitHub repository⁄„You can also build Nu from the latest source on GitHub. This gives you immediate access to the latest features and bug fixes. First, clone the repo:
@
[link: @snippets/installation/git_clone_nu.sh] code
From there, we can build and run Nu with:
@
[link: @snippets/installation/build_nu_from_source.sh] code
You can also build and run Nu in release mode, which enables more optimizations:
@
[link: @snippets/installation/build_nu_from_source_release.sh] code
People familiar with Rust may wonder why we do both a "build" and a "run" step if "run" does a build by default. This is to get around a shortcoming of the new 
``default-run``
 option in Cargo, and ensure that all plugins are built, though this may not be required in the future.
íêê⁄#Title: next:
Path: Building from the GitHub repository
Content:
You can also build Nu from the latest source on GitHub. This gives you immediate access to the latest features and bug fixes. First, clone the repo:
@
[link: @snippets/installation/git_clone_nu.sh] code
From there, we can build and run Nu with:
@
[link: @snippets/installation/build_nu_from_source.sh] code
You can also build and run Nu in release mode, which enables more optimizations:
@
[link: @snippets/installation/build_nu_from_source_release.sh] code
People familiar with Rust may wonder why we do both a "build" and a "run" step if "run" does a build by default. This is to get around a shortcoming of the new 
``default-run``
 option in Cargo, and ensure that all plugins are built, though this may not be required in the future.
